  "text": "Nanoparticles were found to reach the systemic circulation and disseminate to several organs such as the liver, spleen and kidneys [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Kidneys play an important role in eliminating xenobiotics from the body and NPs absorbed in the systemic circulation can be excreted by renal clearance [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Few studies have described the a P < 0.001, b P < 0.01 compared with the normal control group, *** P < 0.001 compared with the n-ZnO-intoxicated group, $$ P ≤ 0.01, $ P ≤ 0.05 compared with the Qur-treated group, πππ P ≤ 0.001, ππ P ≤ 0.01 compared with the combination group, respectively, using ANOVA followed by Bonferroni as a post-ANOVA test.",
